# ==============================================================================
# AstraDB Build Environment Configuration
# ==============================================================================
# This file contains environment variables for building AstraDB
# ==============================================================================

# Proxy Configuration
# Set your proxy URL here. CPM will use these to download dependencies.
# Format: http://host:port or socks5://host:port

# Example for Clash/Clash for Windows (HTTP proxy)
# HTTP_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:7890
# HTTPS_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:7890

# Example for V2Ray (HTTP proxy)
# HTTP_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:10809
# HTTPS_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:10809

# Example for Shadowsocks (SOCKS5 proxy - needs conversion to HTTP)
# HTTP_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:1080
# HTTPS_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:1080

# Your SOCKS5 proxy on port 7897
# Note: Most SOCKS proxy clients also provide an HTTP proxy port.
# Check your proxy client's settings to find the HTTP proxy port.
# For example, Clash typically uses 7890 for HTTP and 7891 for SOCKS5.

# If your proxy client only provides SOCKS5, you may need to use a tool like
# 'socks5h2http' to convert it, or use git's built-in SOCKS5 support:
# git config --global http.proxy socks5://127.0.0.1:7897
# git config --global https.proxy socks5://127.0.0.1:7897

# For now, we'll set the HTTP proxy to your SOCKS proxy port.
# CMake/CPM should be able to handle this, or you can use the system proxy.
HTTP_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:7897
HTTPS_PROXY=http://127.0.0.1:7897

# Alternative: Use SOCKS5 directly (if supported)
# HTTP_PROXY=socks5://127.0.0.1:7897
# HTTPS_PROXY=socks5://127.0.0.1:7897

